'''The Obô Natural Park of Príncipe''' ({{lang-pt|Parque Natural Obô do Príncipe}}) is a natural park of [[São Tomé and Príncipe]], covering 85&nbsp;km² of the island of [[Príncipe]].<ref name="PRI">{{cite web|url=https://arleciosoares13.wordpress.com/areas-protegidas/parque-natural-do-principe/|title=Parque Natural do Príncipe|accessdate=19 October 2018}}</ref> It was established in 2006.<ref>[https://arleciosoares13.files.wordpress.com/2013/10/lei-07-06-parque-natural-do-principe.pdf Lei 07/2006], 13 June 2006</ref> 

==Flora and fauna==
On Príncipe island, fauna includes a frog known as ''[[Phrynobatrachus dispar]]'', birds such as [[Dohrn's thrush-babbler]]  (''Horizorhinus dohrni''), the [[Príncipe kingfisher]], [[ Principe starling]] and the [[Príncipe thrush]] (''Turdus xanthorhynchus''), and the [[grey parrot]] (''Psittacus erithacus''), and a moth such as ''[[Agrotera albalis]]''.

